WebOodi tool gives a command line interface to (HUT) WebOodi with
some additional features. Currently it can export iCalendar schedule
of lectures, exercises and exams of all courses where user has
registered.

WebOodi tool is released under the GPL.


Example use case:

Login to WebOodi and fetch all relevant data:
$ weboodi --save-password sync

Export iCal calendar of all registered courses:
$ weboodi ical --reg > output.ics

Display some info
$ weboodi list

"What's next"
$ weboodi next


Later: Export new calendar, but also resync all data from WebOodi
$ weboodi --sync ical > output.ics
